<inglise> THE GOVERNING COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN CENTRAL BANK, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA KESKPANGA N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Statute of the European System of Central Banks and of the European Central Bank (hereinafter referred to as the "Statute") and in particular to Article 19.1 and the first indent of Article 47.2 thereof, to Council Regulation (EC) No 2531/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the application of minimum reserves by the European Central Bank(1) and to Council Regulation (EC) No 2532/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the powers of the European Central Bank to impose sanctions(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Keskpankade S&uuml;steemi ja Euroopa Keskpanga p&otilde;hikirja (edaspidi "p&otilde;hikiri"), eelk&otilde;ige selle artiklit 19.1 ja artikli 47.2 esimest taanet, n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2531/98 kohustuslike reservide kohaldamise kohta Euroopa Keskpanga poolt (1) ning n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2532/98 Euroopa Keskpanga volituste kohta rakendada sanktsioone, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EC) No 2533/98 of 23 November 1998 concerning the collection of statistical information by the European Central Bank(3) (ECB), and in particular to Articles 5(1) and 6(4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 23. novembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2533/98 statistilise teabe kogumise kohta Euroopa Keskpanga (EKP) poolt, (3) eelk&otilde;ige selle artikli 5 l&otilde;iget 1 ja artikli 6 l&otilde;iget 4, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to ECB Regulation (EC) No 2818/98 of 1 December 1998 on the application of minimum reserves (ECB/1998/15) (4), as amended by ECB Regulation (EC) No 1921/2000(5), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse EKP 1. detsembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2818/98 kohustuslike reservide kohaldamise kohta (EKP/1998/15), (4) nagu seda on muudetud EKP m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1921/2000, (5) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to ECB Regulation (EC) No 2819/98 of 1 December 1998 concerning the consolidated balance sheet of the monetary financial institutions sector (ECB/1998/16) (6), as amended by ECB Regulation (EC) No 1921/2000(7), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse EKP 1. detsembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 monetaar-finantsasutuste sektori koondbilansi kohta (EKP/1998/16) (6), nagu seda on muudetud EKP m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1921/2000, (7) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the contribution by the General Council of the European Central Bank, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Keskpanga &uuml;ldn&otilde;ukogu toetust, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The introduction of the euro in Greece as of 1 January 2001 entails the submission of credit institutions located in Greece and branches in Greece of credit institutions to the ESCB's minimum reserves system as of the same date. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) seoses euro kasutuselev&otilde;tuga Kreekas alates 1. jaanuarist 2001 peavad Kreekas asuvad krediidiasutused ja krediidiasutuste Kreeka filiaalid nimetatud kuup&auml;evast kuuluma EKPS kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemi; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The integration of these entities into the ESCB's minimum reserves system requires the adoption of transitional provisions in order to ensure smooth integration without creating a disproportionate burden for credit institutions in participating Member States, including Greece. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) nimetatud asutuste integreerimiseks EKPS kohustuslike reservide s&uuml;steemi on tarvis vastu v&otilde;tta &uuml;leminekus&auml;tted sujuva integreerumise tagamiseks, ilma et osalevatele liikmesriikidele, sealhulgas Kreeka krediidiasutusele, pandaks lisakoormust; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) The conjunction of Article 5 of the Statute and Article 10 of the Treaty establishing the European Community implies an obligation for Member States to design and implement at national level all the appropriate measures in order to carry out the collection of the statistical information needed to fulfil the ECB's statistical reporting requirements and the timely preparation in the field of statistics in order for them to become participating Member States, </inglise>
<eesti> 3) p&otilde;hikirja artikli 5 ning Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingu artikli 10 koosm&otilde;just tuleneb liikmesriikide jaoks kohustus kavandada ja v&otilde;tta riiklikul tasandil k&otilde;ik meetmed, mida nad peavad vajalikuks, et koguda EKP statistiliste andmete esitamise n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku statistilist teavet ning teha statistika valdkonnas &otilde;igeaegselt ettevalmistusi, selleks et saada osalevateks liikmesriikideks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Transitional provisions </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;leminekus&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise> The transitional provisions for the application of minimum reserves by the ECB following the introduction of the euro in Greece are set out in the Annex to the present Regulation which shall form an integral part of this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti> EKP poolt kohustuslike reservide kohaldamise &uuml;leminekus&auml;tted Kreekas euro kasutuselev&otilde;tu j&auml;rgseks ajaks on s&auml;testatud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas, mis moodustab k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lahutamatu osa. </eesti>
<inglise> In the absence of specific provisions in this Regulation, the provisions of Regulations (EC) No 2818/98 and (EC) No 2819/98 shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui k&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus konkreetseid s&auml;tteid ei sisalda, kohaldatakse m&auml;&auml;ruste (E&Uuml;) nr 2818/98 ja (E&Uuml;) nr 2819/98 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Entry into force </inglise>
<eesti> J&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions set out in the Annex of this Regulation shall only be effective with regard to the first maintenance periods of 2001. </inglise>
